FBIS4-26870 "drchi124_a_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Reception Marks Principles of Peaceful Coexistence Reception Marks Principles of Peaceful Coexistence Commemoration of 40th Anniversary OW2706113394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1119 GMT 27 Jun 94 OW2706113394 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, June 27 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries hosted a reception here this evening to commemorate the 40th anniversary of the proclamation of the five principles of peaceful co-existence. Qi Huaiyuan, president of the association, made a speech at the reception. Qian Zhengying, vice-chairwoman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National Committee and president of the China-India Friendship Association, Indian Ambassador to China Chandra Shekhar Dasgupta and Myanmar Ambassador to China H.E. U Set were present at the reception.
